<br>
1.  TLC promotes uber &quot;phat lewt&quot; &amp; level chasing play over roleplay.  It gives a big advantage to those with money to pay lowbies to quest for them.  It gives a big advantage to those with two accounts and two computers (can farm low items with blur, atone, FD, etc.).  It gives a bigger advantage to those that read spoiler sites than it does for non-TLC -- it almost makes reading spoiler sites essential.<br>
<br>
2. TLC breaks quests.  You can't do quest discovery.  Many quests involve killing green creatures for no-drop items (which of course trivial-out here).  You can't even see what you might have obtained when trying a new quest with TLC in place.  Basically, you have to wait until someone else solves it and posts the spoiler on the web.<br>
<br>
3. TLC promotes farming.  You *MUST* pay a farmer for blocked items.  There is no way around that other than two computers (see point 1).  TLC encourages lowbies to farm rare TLC blocked items and charge outrageous sums for them.  Without TLC, you have the choice to pay a farmer or camp it yourself.  With TLC, you simply pay -- no choice.  You need to empty your wallet on a newbie raising plat to buy ethereal mist or fire up your 2nd comp/account (y'all do have a two comps and accounts, right?).<br>
<br>
Most people that support TLC are non-roleplaying web d00ds that want to kick back and let someone else solve the quests for them.  After the spoiler is on the web, they have no problems not doing the quest themselves, but rather reading about it and paying someone to do it for them.  Those that aren't web-d00ds are perma-lowbies that want to charge outrageous prices to farm trivial items so they can buy gear they have no intention of leveling up to obtain themselves.  Most generalizations are ridiculous.<br>
<br>
When you see a level 1 player in full planar armor, I think you'll change your mind about how good TLC is.  Or maybe not.  Maybe you're one of those that wants to buy planar on ebay instead of hunt for it yourself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uchiporama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chiporama</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 7:45:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TLC is really not a problem for ..</span><hr size=1> Most of your points are baseless statements lacking any hard evidence (other than opinion) to back them.<br>
<br>
Addressing your Points:<br>
<br>
1) &quot;TLC promotes uber &quot;phat lewt&quot; &amp; level chasing play over roleplay... it gives advantages....&quot;<br>
False:<br>
- TLC does not promote 'phat Lewt' or level chasing, especially over Roleplaying.   You give no solid example of how the TLC directly causes either of these by itself (IE - a person with 2 computers and 2 accounts still holds that advantage without the TLC.  And people will still read spolier sights to solve quests, and you can still solve quest without reading spoiler sights.).    <br>
<br>
2) &quot;TLC breaks quests. You can't do quest discovery&quot;<br>
False:<br>
- Most quests tell you what you need, either by quest NPC or book in library.   In most quests, you do not 'discover' a quest when you kill a mob (ie - the mob drop does not suddenly tell you about the quest).<br>
<br>
3) &quot;TLC promotes farming. You *MUST* pay a farmer for blocked items&quot;<br>
False:<br>
- Paying farmers is not the *ONLY* way to obtain blocked items.  You can merchant mine, plan ahead and farm yourself when with in the TLC, have a guildie get it for you, find a newbee not charging insane prices, etc.  Farming on one level or another is a part of the game (it is part of the player economy).  <br>
<br>
4) &quot;Most people that support TLC are non-roleplaying web d00ds that want to kick back and let someone else solve the quests for them&quot;<br>
- False<br>
You have no evidence and make a  broad baseless acusation.<br>
<br>
5) &quot;When you see a level 1 player in full planar armor, I think you'll change your mind about how good TLC is.&quot;<br>
- False<br>
It is near impossible for a level 1 to make enough money farming anything to make the money to purchase a full set of planar armor (at a resonable price, not at 1 plat per piece).<br>
<br>
6) &quot;Maybe you're one of those that wants to buy planar on ebay instead of hunt for it yourself.&quot;<br>
- False<br>
Do you know me?  Did I indicate this in my posts? Again, another example of baseless statements.<br>
<br>
In general your arguments are baseless acusations to support a rule that you disagree with.  You castigate vaild arguments against your statements, rather than offer strong evidence to support your position.  In fact, most of your statements would are better arguments for the the TLC (in that without it, most of the issues you stated would be rampant, just as they are on other normal servers).<br>
<br>
Your arguments seem to simply elude to you haveing negative experiences with the TLC.  That you probably had negative experiences in attempting to purchase TLC blocked items, and that you feel 'cheated' by the TLC barrier that you are faced with.  Now I do not know you, so I am only making an educated guess based on your posts rather than following your example of making wild acusations, disparaging remarks and baseless statements to support my position.<br>
<br>
It would be nice to hear some 'hard' facts why the TLC should be removed.  What are some quests that are completely unsolvable because of the TLC (and it can only be fixed by removing the TLC).  How does the TLC make the game unplayable?  Not the 'it makes my life difficult so remove it' opinion.<br>
<br>
