<br>
In simple words of little sylable the reason TLC should be removed is that it forces farming instead of permiting people to solve quests themselves.  When faced with a TLC blocked item, you are required to pay outrageous sums for a simple to obtain item, delevel yourself (absolutely NOT an option that should even be considered), or use a 2nd-comp mule.  Most do not have a second comp+account.  That means large sums, which are not available until you are high level.  So, TLC promotes leveling and &quot;phat lewt&quot; gathering so you can afford to pay the farmers.<br>
<br>
TLC doesn't stop farming.  It just makes it more exclusive.  Guess what I found when I went to wisp island to get some xp and cash?  A high level druid and mule on 2nd comp farming every wisp on the island.  Guess what I find when hiring lowbies for quests?  Complete disinterest.  I don't blaim them.  I can't afford to pay much at all, nor do I wish to.<br>
<br>
And, yes, it completely removes all hope of quest discovery from the game.  I did quite a bit of that on my other server.  Some of the most worthwhile quests do not tell you which mob to kill or what to do with the item or even what the item is (eg. monk shackles).  You often have to kill armies of green things and then use an identify spell on everything that drops.  If things don't drop due to TLC, you can't solve the quest.<br>
<br>
The iksar shackle quest was so buggy that I had leveled my monk to 57 before they finally fixed it.  So, I'm supposed to delevel to 15 to finish it?  I'm supposed to find and pay a lowbie to spend 20-50 hours camping green junk when we don't even know if it's really fixed or what we really need? It took 4 rounds of &quot;we fixed it!&quot;, &quot;uh, no you didn't!&quot;  Ask a friend to do that camp?  I wouldn't even dream of it.  I'm not that cruel to my friends.<br>
<br>
Now for myself, I have a 2nd comp and account.  TLC is no hardship for me personally -- other than having to maintain a mule of the right level.  I'm thinking about the folks that are real newbies, don't have two accounts, don't have two computers, haven't played multiple characters to post-50, or don't read the web.  That covers most people.  They're great people.  They make this server so much more fun than a regular blue server.  TLC will squash them flat.  It turns FV from a RP server into an RP/experts server.<br>
<br>
TLC is for elitists.  I like newbies, especially the non-begging variety, which seems to be all FV has.  FV has great newbies!  I seriously dislike pretention and elitist snobbery; eg. &quot;You knew about TLC when coming here.  *I* can get a round it. I don't give a damn if you can or not, so lump it or leave it.&quot;  Hell, I can get around it, too.  Most can't.  I do give a damn about them.  So, I don't like TLC.<br>
<br>
If all I cared about was myself, I'd say keep the TLC and get rid of the alignments.  Then I could make a lizard monk that could group with everyone and still twink my second char with planar armor.  It will just be a while before I can do that.  I'm sure others are already doing it -- they're just not being obvious about it.<br>
<br>
BTW, I'm not going to go into the exploits TLC permits for obvious reasons.  Think about it, though.  Almost nothing is no-drop.  If I was selfish, I'd be embracing TLC like a twin seperated since birth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 10:48:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin quests...</span><hr size=1> As to the starting quests for the Vah Shir:<br>
<br>
If you're not a Vah Shir, you can't do them.  Period.  You have to turn in your Acryllia Sheet in order to activate them, at one stage or another.<br>
<br>
They are completeable.  A bit tough, I'll grant you, but they can be done.  I've done them.<br>
<br>
I like TLC.  Not because of the individual restriction but because of the overall effect it has had on the server.  Players on FV are smart.  Really smart.  Our resident uber guild, FnF, is not filled with d00ds and l33t3s but rather thoughtful and considered tactical players.  Our general population has a better understanding of the mechanics of the game and the way that classes can interact than any other server that I've seen, and I've seen several.<br>
<br>
Newbies to the game are learning at the very start how to run their characters effectively.  People are more polite to each other because the only way to erase your rep is to restart your one and only character.  Grouping is stronger because we HAVE to form tight-knit groups.<br>
<br>
Yes, server population is low.  That's because we're only getting organic growth and not server-changes, for the most part.  Those who wanted to acquire rather than experience have stayed away, or left almost immediately.  Our new adds are people who are brand new to the game, and that's a good thing.<br>
<br>
So, my vote:  Napster bad.  TLC good.<br>
<br>
