<br>
BTW, I don't think TLC breeds intelligence -- shrewd cunning perhaps, but not intelligence.  It requires that you do three things: 1. wait until someone else has solved the quest and posted it on the web.  2. hunt the web for spoilers.  3. find a way around the TLC.  So, it seems to me that it breeds behavior that is somewhat lazy and exploitive rather than encouraging people to figure out and do quests for themselves.<br>
<br>
For most servers, 1&amp;2 are optional.  You can choose to be lazy and wait or you can choose to solve it yourself.  Here, you must wait.  That's the problem.  You can't even read about a quest and decide to go off and do it on your own time.  You have to research mob levels and trivial points, pick your level window, and recruit lowbies to kill for you.  You can't do your research in-game, the /con system will only tell you all the mobs are green, not where they're trivial.  This makes questing far harder here.  So much harder that unless the reward is substantial, most people won't bother.  Kinda takes the &quot;quest&quot; out of Everquest.<br>
<br>
If every single quest item was exempted from the TLC, then I'd have no problem with it.  I see that as essentially removing TLC from the server.  We don't need TLC because we don't have a farmer problem.  What we have is a population problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/31/01 4:01:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FYI</span><hr size=1> However, without TLC we would have a farming problem.  Not from anyone present, I don't think (although there are lots of folks on this server who don't post to or read this board) but rather from the hoards who would descend upon us.  I don't doubt for a moment that a large number of individuals would come over from other servers, powerlevel themselves up in a matter of a week or two, and then start farming Guk.  For starters.  The server would be awash in no time in ph@t l3wts and the entire purpose of putting the hardship package in place for this server would be defeated.<br>
<br>
Now, I have no hard and fast evidence that this would _definitely happen_ but then again, I have seen what happens to other servers.<br>
<br>
I don't think FV is going to be around very long in its present form.  The population is too low for it to be profitable, and I think we'll probably be merged with another server.  When and if that happens, you'll get your wish.  TLC will be gone, but so will everything else.  If this server can't support itself with a player base then that means that this experiment is a failure.<br>
<br>
We can offset this by, instead of complaining about the strictures imposed upon us, succeeding despite them.  I didn't have walkthroughs when I started my Vah Shir, but I managed to run my quests.  I didn't get TLC'd, although I came close.  I didn't (and still don't) know what I'm walking into as far as the Sonic Wolf Bane Weapon quest, but I figure I'll work it out when I get there.<br>
<br>
This server makes me level slow.  I don't mind that, because everyone else is levelling at about the same pace (with some exceptions).  Anyhoo, best of luck. <p>Denoi Fishwhiskers<BR>
